The paper deals with the spanning properties of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of cones and projections suggests a geometric approach, further supporting the cs.CG category. The paper also involves analysis of algorithms and optimization, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI). Finally, the lack of specific applications or datasets suggests that the paper is not focused on machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV).
